title: @OspreyVB Back on the Road with Tough Matches at USC Upstate and Kennesaw State
text: (10th, .289) are listed in the Top 10. Let's Play 5: Each of the last four weekends has included one five-set match for the Ospreys. UNF had its first five-set match of the season against Eastern Kentucky on Sept. 4. Since then, the Ospreys have gone and won in five sets against Florida Atlantic (Sept. 12), Wright State (Sept. 18) and Jacksonville (Sept. 25). UNF is 4-0 this season in five sets. USC Upstate: Only other Atlantic Sun school to enter the weekend with double-digit wins... spent majority of its first month of competition on the road and is only 2-0 at home thus far in the season... began Atlantic Sun play with a 3-2 loss at Kennesaw State on Saturday... leads the Atlantic Sun in kills (13.55), aces (1.83) and digs (18.34)... Shannon Weiss (0.53) and Madison Haake (0.48) ranked No. 1 and No. 2 in the Atlantic Sun in aces per set... Haake averages 3.13 kills per set, while Emily Koelling has a team-best 173 total kills... Lexi Gober averages 9.31 assists per set... Weiss is digging 4.58 balls per set. UNF-USC Upstate Series: UNF leads the all-time series 31-7, but last season, each team won 3-2 on its home court. Kennesaw State: Has won its last two matches, both of which were at home and included a 3-1 victory over Georgia Tech (Sept. 18) and a 3-2 edging of USC Upstate... begins the weekend on Friday night against Jacksonville... Saturday's match finishes a five-match homestand... has limited opponents to just a .157 hitting percentage... a trio of Owls -- Sydni Shelton (2.93), Kelly Marcinek (2.82) and Anaiah Boyer (2.63) -- average over 2.50 kills per set... Shelton was tabbed as the Atlantic Sun's Player and Freshman of the Week on Sept. 28... Kristi Piedimonte averages 9.62 assists per set, while Katarina Morton is averaging 4.49 digs per set. UNF-Kennesaw State Series: Kennesaw State leads the all-time series 8-6, but UNF swept last season's series, winning 3-1 in Jacksonville on Oct. 17 and then 3-2 on Nov. 1 in Kennesaw.
